Mexico’s Coffee Exports Increased 1.9% in April, Amecafe Says

-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-05-11T07:55:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/mexico-s-coffee-exports-increased-1-9-in-april-amecafe-says.html
Mexico ’s coffee exports rose 1.9
percent in April, according to figures from the country’s coffee
association, known as Amecafe.  Shipments climbed to 313,525 bags from 307,827 bags a year
earlier, Amecafe said in an e-mailed statement yesterday.
Exports for the season that started Oct. 1 fell 15 percent to
1.37 million bags.  Mexico’s coffee production in the current season is
estimated at 4 million bags, Rodolfo Trampe Taubert, the
association’s executive coordinator, said March 31.  A bag of coffee weighs 60 kilograms (132 pounds).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isis Almeida in London at 
